    {
        "content": "<p>Hey, given simple graphs <code>x y z</code> with <code>x ≤ y</code> and <code>disjoint x z</code>, I'd like to get <code>x ≤ y \\ z</code>. I've searched through the different <code>order</code>-related lemmas but haven't found anything close to it, not even <code>x ≤ x \\ z</code>. Am I searching wrong?</p>",
        "id": 312301882,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémi Bottinelli",
        "timestamp": 1669447728
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/le_sdiff_iff\">docs#le_sdiff_iff</a> isn't what you want but you should be able to generalize <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/set.subset_diff\">docs#set.subset_diff</a> to generalized_boolean_algebra</p>",
        "id": 312302914,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1669448545
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, so it really is just a missing lemma</p>",
        "id": 312303074,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémi Bottinelli",
        "timestamp": 1669448657
